In order to set up the environment and run the tests for the `fmtlib/fmt` repository, I will gather information from several key configuration files.

First, I will examine `CMakeLists.txt` to understand the build system, required C++ standard, and any specific dependencies declared within the project's build configuration.

Next, I will analyze `.travis.yml` as it typically contains the exact commands used by continuous integration to set up the environment, build the project, and execute tests. This will be invaluable for identifying required tools, compilers, and test commands.

Finally, I will check `README.rst` and `CONTRIBUTING.md` for any high-level setup instructions or common development practices that might not be immediately obvious from the build scripts alone.

Here are the API calls I will make:

```json
[
  {
    "api_name": "browse_file_for_environment_info",
    "arguments": {
      "file_path": "CMakeLists.txt",
      "custom_query": "Identify C++ standard, build steps, and declared dependencies."
    }
  },
  {
    "api_name": "browse_file_for_environment_info",
    "arguments": {
      "file_path": ".travis.yml",
      "custom_query": "Extract commands for environment setup, building, and running tests, including compiler versions and any required apt packages."
    }
  },
  {
    "api_name": "browse_file_for_environment_info",
    "arguments": {
      "file_path": "README.rst",
      "custom_query": "Look for general setup instructions and how to build/test the project."
    }
  },
  {
    "api_name": "browse_file_for_environment_info",
    "arguments": {
      "file_path": "CONTRIBUTING.md",
      "custom_query": "Check for developer setup guidelines or specific testing instructions."
    }
  }
]
```
